<L>__{exterior mess hall. early morning.}
<A>__{sergeant fry strides into the middle of the throng of soldiers.}
<C>__{sergeant fry}
<D>__{gentlemen! gentlemen! it falls on me to give you some important news. at eleven o'clock today, in two minutes time the war will come to an end.}
<A>__{shock from the troops. strangely muted. not the explosion of emotion you might have expected. albert enters, his eyes still red, but no longer bandaged.}
<C>__{sergeant fry }
<D>__{the king and queen thank you for your service. we have been victorious even if at a higher price than many of us might have imagined.}
<C>__{sergeant fry }
<D>__{when the bells ring out and they will in a moment, for the first time for four years let us remember our brothers fallen in the field. and thank god for the end of this struggle and victory.}
<A>__{and, in the distance, the church bells ring.}
